<subSubSection id="B1A7ECF1F278142773E5EDFD516D2FD2" box="[199,1352,1977,2004]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F902BF7AF278142773E5EDFD516D2FD2" blockId="17.[151,1436,1833,2040]" box="[199,1352,1977,2004]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="CBC96368F278142773E5EDFD55442FD2" bold="true" box="[199,353,1977,2004]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from three quite distant (located 
<quantity id="3E45129FF2781427700DEDFD57992FD5" box="[815,956,1977,2004]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="km" value="400.0" valueMax="500.0" valueMin="300.0">300–500 km</quantity>
from each other) localities in 
<collectingCountry id="81AAFFEAF2781427762FEDFE51612FD2" box="[1293,1348,1978,2004]" name="Peru" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Peru</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
